    <note type="biography">
        <p>Botanist and schoolteacher. Schoolteacher at St Peter’s School, York, 1839–44. Collected plant specimens in the Pyrenees, 1845–6; in South America, 1849–64. PhD, Imperial German Academy, 1864. Retired in poor health to Coneysthorpe, Yorkshire, where he worked on his plant collections.</p></note>
